<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UCLA 93, Arizona State 81 -- Natalie Williams grabbed a Pacific 10 women's 
record of 25 rebounds and scored 32 points to lead Bruins over the Sun Devils 
at UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams bettered the conference rebound mark of 23 that she had shared with 
three others. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bruins (14-8, 9-4) rallied from a 48-41 deficit early in the second half 
with an 18-2 run. 
</P>
<P>
 Tiffany Krahenbuhl led the Sun Devils (3-18, 1-12) with 25 points. 
</P>
