<HEADLINE>
<P>
'94 WINTER OLYMPICS / LILLEHAMMER; NOTEBOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Given the recent death of teammate Ulrike Maier, killed in a Jan. 29 downhill 
crash, the Austrian women might be forgiven for their lackluster performances. 
</P>
<P>
 American Julie Parisien, who has found it difficult to ski since the death of 
her brother more than a year ago, said she understands. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's just been really tough on them," Parisien said. "Every time they're in 
the start gate, I'm sure they're thinking about Ulli. Every time I'm in there 
I'm thinking, 'Wow, did Ulli talk to these people before she went down? Did she 
click into her bindings the same way?' " All this goes through your head, 
because she was so close to all of us." 
</P>
