</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tim Tetrault of Norwich, Vt., who competes on the U.S. Nordic combined team, 
slipped on the ice in downtown Lillehammer on Saturday night and suffered a 
broken left leg. 
</P>
<P>
 Tetrault, who had finished 30th in the individual Nordic event -- it combines 
ski jumping and cross-country skiing -- was also scheduled to compete in the 
team version of the event, starting Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 He was treated by the U.S. team's medical staff, who X-rayed the injury and 
put a cast on Tetrault's leg. MIKE KUPPER 
</P>
