'94 WINTER OLYMPICS / LILLEHAMMER; NOTEBOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROSS NEWHAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 U.S. bobsled Coach Joey Kilburn wasn't specifically addressing the failed 
attempt to replace Randy Jones with Jeff Woodard as the pusher on Brian 
Shimer's two-man sled, but he said there is a need to change the rules that 
thwarted the move. 
</P>
<P>
 "Look at the number of sports where the coach has the discretion to make a 
move in the best interest of the team," he said."Right now, we're handcuffed. 
We can't make a change unless there's an injury or the athlete agrees to step 
down. 
</P>
<P>
 "We need to emphasize to the board of the federation and the USOC that we need 
to have that leeway. We should be able to make a change based on hard facts." 
ROSS NEWHAN 
</P>
