<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: JAGUARS DECIDE ON COUGHLIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Boston College Coach Tom Coughlin will become the coach and director of 
football operations for the NFL's Jacksonville Jaguars. 
</P>
<P>
 The expansion club has called a news conference for this afternoon, although 
Jaguar president David Selden would not confirm the hiring. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Chet Gladchuk, Boston College's athletic director, said Coughlin made 
the decision Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Coughlin was 21-13-1 at Boston College in three years, taking the Eagles to 
bowl games the last two years. He went 4-7 in his first season after succeeding 
Jack Bicknell. Coughlin's biggest victory, by 41-39, cost Notre Dame last 
season's national championship. Pro Basketball  
</P>
<P>
 The Detroit Pistons traded center Olden Polynice to the Sacramento Kings for 
center Pete Chilcutt and a first-round pick. The trade came a day after the 
Pistons rejected trading Polynice and forward David Wood to the Kings for 
center Duane Causwell. The Pistons said Causwell failed a physical examination 
because of a "pre-existing condition." 
</P>
<P>
 Christian Laettner was suspended for today's game after being ejected from the 
Minnesota Timberwolves' practice after a heated exchange with assistant coach 
Bob Weinhauer. Miscellany  
</P>
<P>
 Michael Chang beat Paul Haarhuis, 6-3, 6-2, to win the U.S. Indoor title in 
Philadelphia. . . . Top-seeded Martina Navratilova beat Julie Halard of France, 
7-5, 6-3, to win the Paris Women's Open. The victory extended Navratilova's 
record of singles titles to 167. 
</P>
<P>
 Pitchers Dave Stewart and Todd Stottlemyre of the World Series champion 
Toronto Blue Jays were arrested in Tampa, Fla., after allegedly scuffling with 
police outside a nightclub. 
</P>
<P>
 Ireland's Eamonn Coghlan ran the mile in 3 minutes 58.15 seconds to become the 
first man over 40 to run a mile in less than four minutes. Coghlan's 
performance came at Harvard's Albert E. Gordon track in Boston. Coghlan, 41, 
broke his Masters indoor mile record of 4:01.39. 
</P>
<P>
 Cory McClenathan (top fuel), John Force (funny cars) and Scott Geoffrion (pro 
stock) won titles at the Ford Quality Care Nationals at Chandler, Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
 Four months before the World Cup, Saudi Arabia has fired Dutch soccer coach 
Leo Beenhakker, saying his style was not appropriate for the team. 
</P>
<P>
 Tommy Morrison stopped Tui Toia with a third-round knockout in a heavyweight 
bout at Biloxi, Miss. 
</P>
