<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; NEIGHBORS POLLED OVER FIREWORKS SHOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents near Ventura College are being polled to see if they object to a 
proposed July 4 fireworks show at the campus. 
</P>
<P>
 The college and the Ventura Rotary Club are considering putting on the show, 
which would be the first Independence Day fireworks display in the city since 
1992. 
</P>
<P>
 The show would be staged on the college's softball field, and tickets would be 
sold for seating in the fenced area, according to a flyer seeking neighbors' 
comments. Neighbors would each receive two complimentary tickets. Security and 
supervised parking would be provided; alcohol would be prohibited. 
</P>
<P>
 "We need the cooperation of all the neighbors," said Norman Blacher, 
president-elect of the Ventura Rotary Club. "We're hoping they would go along." 
TRACY WILSON 
</P>
