<HEADLINE>
<P>
SLEEPING MAN ROLLS OVER ONTO BABY DAUGHTER, CRITICALLY INJURING HER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man sleeping in bed next to his 2-month-old daughter Sunday accidentally 
rolled over onto the baby, crushing her, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The infant remained in critical condition at Children's Hospital of Orange 
County, according to police investigators. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they got a frantic call about 12:25 a.m. from the child's mother, 
who lives in the 200 block of Avocado Street. 
</P>
<P>
 She had just returned home from work, awakened her husband and discovered the 
infant pinned beneath him. The child, she told police, had stopped breathing. 
</P>
<P>
 A dispatcher instructed the parents on how to perform cardiopulmonary 
resuscitation on the child, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A team of officers arrived minutes later and continued efforts to revive the 
baby until paramedics arrived. 
</P>
<P>
 The infant was first taken to Hoag Hospital in Newport Beach, then moved to 
Children's Hospital in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 Police declined to release the names of the parents until the investigation is 
completed. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said the incident appears to have been a freak accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
