157 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; DAMAGED COLLEGE LIBRARY TO REOPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Moorpark College library is scheduled to reopen Tuesday after a month of 
work to repair damage sustained in the Jan. 17 earthquake, part of $100,000 in 
damage across the campus. 
</P>
<P>
 Loose and fallen plaster from the building's central ceiling and cracked walls 
had to be repaired, and 3,000 books that spilled onto the floor had to be 
replaced before the main section of the library could reopen. 
</P>
<P>
 It was declared structurally safe earlier this month, but has remained closed 
while workers replaced overhead lights in the building. 
</P>
<P>
 However, the library's upstairs classrooms, which suffered only cosmetic 
damage, have been in use since Feb. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to library work, the college also had to repair damage at the 
gymnasium, where overhead lighting fixtures came loose and fell onto support 
beams, and where an air-conditioning duct crashed to the floor. The gym was 
reopened by the first week of February. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
