<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: HOT LINE SET UP FOR WATER-RELATED ISSUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Regional Water Quality Control Board has set up a hot line for 
Ventura County businesses seeking information about waste discharge 
requirements and other water-related issues. 
</P>
<P>
 The hot line, coupled with a new business assistance office, will enable 
callers to speak with the board's staff between 8 a.m. and 4 p.m. weekdays. 
</P>
<P>
 "The board's goal in setting up this office is to help the public and the 
regulated community get through the permitting process quickly and 
efficiently," said Robert Ghirelli, regional board executive director. 
</P>
<P>
 "We want to make the process less burdensome for the public by helping people 
make sense out of the water quality rules and regulations with which they must 
comply," he said in a statement released by the board. 
</P>
<P>
 The board oversees permitting and regulation of issues relating to waste 
discharge and water quality in Ventura County. 
</P>
<P>
 The hot line number is (800) 500-8008. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</TEXT>
