<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 ROBBERIES UNDER INVESTIGATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies late Sunday were investigating two armed robberies that 
occurred half an hour apart at a liquor store and convenience market in the 
Montalvo and Saticoy areas. 
</P>
<P>
 The first occurred at 6:30 p.m. at Log Cabin Liquor on Alameda Avenue in 
Montalvo.The second happened at 6:55 p.m. at Le Town market on Azahar Street in 
Saticoy. 
</P>
<P>
 In both robberies, two suspects entered the store brandishing handguns. The 
owner or employees were then ordered to lie on the floor while one of the 
suspects scooped money from the till. During the second robbery, the suspects 
spoke Spanish. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's Lt. Gary Backman said everything about the two robberies appeared 
similar except for the description of the suspects' ethnicity. The victims of 
the first robbery described the robbers as white males in their teens. In the 
second robbery, the suspects were said to be Latino males in their late teens. 
JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
