<P>
PAIR OF PHARMACISTS ARE TRUE ANGELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Your editorial "A Balm Amid the Pain of the Quake" (Jan. 30) concerning 
Valley Drug in North Hollywood was right on the mark. 
</P>
<P>
 I am a hospice nurse who deals with Valley Drug on a daily basis. Kinder, more 
attentive, more helpful, more concerned pharmacists are not to be found. 
</P>
<P>
 On the day of the earthquake, Irving Reitzenstein not only had the medicine I 
needed for my patient's severe pain, he gave my patient's care-giver enough 
medicine to get her through until she was able to reach her own pharmacy. 
</P>
<P>
 Pharmacists Ralph Figueroa and Irving Reitzenstein are true angels. 
</P>
<P>
 KATHERINE F. LILLY 
</P>
<P>
 North Hollywood 
