<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOKA 'UNIVERSITY' REALLY ISN'T ONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Why does The Times insist on referring to Soka as Soka University? 
</P>
<P>
 It has neither a faculty, curriculum nor student body that would make it a 
university. Because some bureaucrats recognize it as a university for tax 
purposes does not in fact make it a university. For that matter, Los Angeles 
County does not recognize them as being a certified school, much less a 
university. As a result, Soka is required to pay property tax. 
</P>
<P>
 Your Soka article of Dec. 12 had Soka University across the page in huge 
letters. What's up? 
</P>
<P>
 BILL WELLS 
</P>
<P>
 Malibu 
</P>
</TEXT>
