<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLDEN WEST GETS TOP PLAYOFF SEEDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golden West is the top-seeded team in the 16-team Southern California playoff 
pairings, which were announced Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rustlers (29-4), who won the Orange Empire Conference title, were one of 
five conference teams to make the playoffs, which start at 7 p.m. 
Wednesday.Riverside, Cypress, Orange Coast and Fullerton also made the field. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West plays host to No. 16 Oxnard (8-20) in a 7 p.m. contest. The winner 
plays the winner of No. 9 Fullerton (19-14) at No. 8 San Diego Mesa (19-8). 
</P>
<P>
 In another bracket: No. 15 Santa Monica (12-15) is at No. 2 Los Angeles Harbor 
(26-6) and No. 10 Southwestern (16-8) is at No. 7 Cerritos (20-10). 
</P>
<P>
 In another bracket: No. 14 Canyons (18-12) is at No. 3 Riverside (25-9) and 
Chaffey (19-11) is at No. 6 Orange Coast (19-12). 
</P>
<P>
 In another bracket: No. 13 Chaffey (14-8) is at No. 4 Ventura (25-5) and No. 
12 Los Angeles Trade Tech (19-8) is at No. 5 Cypress (22-9). 
</P>
<P>
 The winner of each bracket advances to the State tournament March 3-5 at 
Solano College in Suisun City. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West, which has won five consecutive conference titles, have advanced 
to the last seven State tournaments. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rustlers have reached the final four the last four years, winning State 
titles in 1990 and 1991. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
