<HEADLINE>
<P>
SADDLEBACK ENDS SUCCESSFUL HAWAIIAN TRIP WITH SWEEP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback completed a five-game series Sunday in Hawaii by sweeping a 
nonconference doubleheader from host Hawaii Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
 The Gauchos won the first game, 6-3, in seven innings and the second, 12-4.The 
sweep gave Saddleback a 4-1 record on the trip. All five games were against 
Hawaii Pacific, an NAIA college. Saddleback's only loss was 15-13. 
</P>
<P>
 Darin Mai pitched 6 1/3 innings of hitless relief in the first game to get the 
victory for Saddleback. Mai (1-0) had seven strikeouts. 
</P>
<P>
 David Biddinger had two hits, including a triple, and drove in two runs for 
Saddleback, which scored three runs in the second inning and one each in the 
fourth, sixth and seventh. 
</P>
<P>
 In the second game, Saddleback scored four runs in the second inning and added 
two in the third to open a 6-1 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Pat Antrim had four hits, including two doubles, and Wes Brasher added three 
singles for Saddleback (4-3). Antrim had three RBIs and Brasher drove in two. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago and Cerritos were scheduled to play Sunday in the winners' 
bracket final of the tournament of which the teams are co-host, but the game 
was postponed because of wet grounds. 
</P>
<P>
 The game will be made up at 2 p.m. today at Cerritos. 
</P>
