<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; MCDOWELL'S LOSS STILL A BIG GAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cy Young Award winner Jack McDowell lost his arbitration case Sunday, but the 
$5.3 million he will get is a record for a salary awarded by an arbitrator. 
</P>
<P>
 McDowell, who won in arbitration at $4 million last winter, had asked the 
Chicago White Sox for $6.5 million, which would have been the highest one-year 
contract in baseball history. 
</P>
<P>
 The salary topped the $5 million awarded outfielder Ruben Sierra when he won 
his case against Texas two years ago. 
</P>
