<HEADLINE>
<P>
MONTEREY PARK APARTMENT MANAGER KILLED, SISTER SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A tenant of a Monterey Park apartment building allegedly killed the 
40-year-old manager and critically wounded her twin sister Sunday during a 
dispute, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cesar Valdovinos, 38, fled after the shootings and was still at large late 
Sunday.He should be considered armed and dangerous, Monterey Park Police Lt. 
William Young said. 
</P>
<P>
 The argument started shortly before midnight, when Valdovinos, a tenant, went 
to manager Sally Mandeville's apartment in the 16-unit building to discuss what 
witnesses told police was a money-related matter, Young said. Mandeville's twin 
sister, Shirley Mandeville, was also present. 
</P>
<P>
 After the three argued, Valdovinos left the apartment and returned 10 minutes 
later, and a second argument began, Young said. Valdovinos allegedly pulled a 
pistol and shot Sally Mandeville once in the head, and then shot her sister 
once in the head as she tried to run from the living room. 
</P>
<P>
 Sally Mandeville died at Los Angeles County-USC Medical Center, where her 
sister was listed in critical condition. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities asked that anyone with information about Valdovinos call the 
Monterey Park Police Department or the homicide bureau of the Los Angeles 
County Sheriff's Department. Valdovinos is 6-feet, 1-inch tall, weighs 200 
pounds, and has brown eyes and dark brown hair. He is believed to have fled in 
a blue Pontiac Bonneville, license number 2ESN922. 
</P>
</TEXT>
