<P>
 France's Groupe Bull May Sell Stock to Employees: Jean-Marie Descarpentries, 
chairman of the money-losing, state-owned computer maker, said he would like to 
allocate 15% to 20% of Bull's shares to employees, while allowing two or three 
outside partners to buy 10% to 15% each.Japan's NEC Corp. already owns about 5% 
of Bull's parent company and was cited as a possible candidate. IBM owns 2%. 
The French state owns or controls the rest. 
</P>
