<P>
BRIEFLY: WORKPLACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Drug Abuse on the Job Declines Again, Study Says: The figures declined for the 
sixth straight year, according to the latest data from SmithKline Beechman 
Clinical Laboratories, but it is still a huge problem. The SmithKline Beechman 
Drug Testing Index, a gauge of positive drug tests in the workplace, declined 
to 8.41% in 1993, the lowest level in the past decade, from 8.76% in 1992. The 
decline is due largely to "the heightened focus on education and employee 
assistance programs," said Tobey Dichter of SmithKlein, which conducted more 
than 3 million drug tests last year. 
</P>
