<TEXT>
<P>
 Mexican Trade Deficit Shrinks: The 1993 trade deficit dropped to $13.5 
billion, 15.1% lower than a year earlier, the treasury ministry announced.The 
decrease in the shortfall had been expected and was mainly the result of lower 
growth in imports. Imports, which skyrocketed 24.3% in 1992, rose 5.2% last 
year. No reason was given for the import slowdown. However, the government 
launched a vigorous anti-dumping enforcement campaign last year, which affected 
an array of Chinese products and U.S. steel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
