<TEXT>
<P>
 Swiss Ban Foreign Trucks: In a referendum, 52% of the voters approved a 
proposal to force all truck trailers crossing Switzerland between northern and 
southern Europe to be shipped by railroad within 10 years. Trucks carrying 
goods to or from Switzerland and domestic traffic will be exempt. The outcome 
was a stinging rebuke to the four-party governing coalition, which had argued 
the ban would violate international transport treaties and "provoke politically 
and economically harmful retaliation from abroad." 
</P>
