<TEXT>
<P>
 Monsanto Sues Dairy for Boycotting Genetic Drug: In what appears to be the 
first return-fire in the battle over a genetically engineered drug for cows, 
the St. Louis-based company filed suit last week against Swiss Valley Farms, an 
Iowa cooperative that refuses to buy milk from farmers who treat their cows 
with Monsanto's Posilac.The drug is designed to increase milk production. 
Monsanto's suit claims the dairy's advertised pledge not to accept milk from 
cows treated with the controversial drug "impugns the safety and wholesomeness" 
of milk. Even though the Food and Drug Administration has declared the drug 
safe, opponents are waging a campaign to discourage farmers from using it. 
</P>
