 Bankruptcy Debt Climbs: Debt from bankrupt companies surged in January, with 
businesses increasingly unable to make ends meet as the recession grinds on, a 
debt research company said. Debt from business failures rose 53.1% from 
December's figure, to $4.16 billion, while their number rose 17.9% to 1,104, 
