<HEADLINE>
<P>
CORPORATE SNAPSHOT: IRVINE; GATEWAY COMMUNICATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nature of business: Computer networking and communications products 
</P>
<P>
 Total employees: 47 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange County: 45 
</P>
<P>
 Stock listing in The Times: On Nasdaq "GtwyCm' Ticker symbol: "GWAY" 
</P>
<P>
 Friday's stock close: $0.88 One-week change: Down $0.12 
</P>
<P>
 Analyst review: "Gateway Communications ran into some major problems last 
year, in fact it announced in November that it had retained an investment 
banker to considering several options, including finding a buyer for the 
company. Evidently there have been some negotiations but no further 
announcements have been made. Gateway's stock isn't trading heavily, but the 
price is extremely steady. The trading history back to July of last year shows 
it at a low of three-fourths to a high of just over two dollars a share. It 
remains afloat, despite a third quarter loss. It will be interesting to see 
what develops for it over the next few months, especially with its LAN Expander 
products." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Rich Weinstein, analyst Barber & Bronson, Ft. Lauderdale Revenue in 
millions of dollars '90: $25.0 '91: $24.0 '92: $21.0 3 quarters '92: $16.4 '93: 
$8.3 Profit in millions of dollars '90: 0.5 '91: 0.1 '92: 0.6 3 quarters '92: 
0.5 '93: -1.8 
</P>
<P>
 Corporate outlook: "The results for the third quarter of 1993 reflect 
unrelenting price competition and margin pressure in the LAN adaptor market. 
Although we have recently made substantial staff and expense reductions, 
Gateway will continue to invest very selectively in research and development, 
including our LAN Expander products." -- Dr. Patrick F. Cadigan, chairman/CEO 
