<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE JOB: OCCUPATION: PEDIATRICIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Name: Dr. M. Dev 
</P>
<P>
 Practice: Independent practitioner on staff at Martin Luther Hospital, 
Children's Hospital of Orange County and St. Jude Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Job description: Pediatricians are medical doctors who specialize in caring 
for infants and children. There are numerous sub-specialties in the field, 
including caring for premature infants and for children with cancer, heart 
conditions and other maladies. 
</P>
<P>
 Thumbs up: "I am one of the few pediatricians in the area who accepts Medi-Cal 
patients in addition to those who pay cash or are covered by other forms of 
health insurance. By doing this I know that I am filling a need. I am very 
happy in my work and sleep with a clear conscience because I use my skills to 
help children who would otherwise be neglected." 
</P>
<P>
 Thumbs down: "This kind of practice takes a lot out of you sometimes. It is 
very frustrating and sad to see pregnant teens and very poor people with no 
health insurance trying to cope with sick children. But a person who is down 
will not be down forever if we can offer them a bit of help. The more we 
neglect them, the less hope they will have. I have seen people in very 
difficult circumstances turn their lives around, and I am always trying to 
think of ways to help them raise healthy children." 
</P>
<P>
 Next step: "I am trying to extend my office hours into the evening to make it 
more convenient for working parents to bring their children in for care." 
</P>
<P>
 Advice: "It is increasingly difficult to be an independent practitioner, 
especially with all the changes in the health-care system. I would advise 
someone considering becoming a pediatrician to go where doctors are needed most 
and to do whatever they can to make their practice very personal and caring." 
</P>
<P>
 Salary range: In Orange County pediatricians earn between $80,000 to $200,000 
a year. 
</P>
<P>
 Hours: "I am always on call and work nearly every weekend. When I need to take 
time off, another pediatrician fills in for me, and I do the same for him." 
</P>
<P>
 Educational and training requirements: After finishing medical school, a 
pediatrician is required to complete three years of pediatrics study, followed 
by a three-year fellowship in neonatology, neurology or another pediatric 
sub-specialty. 
</P>
<P>
 Major employers: Health maintenance organizations and independent medical 
practices. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information: Contact the Orange County Chapter of the American 
Academy of Pediatrics at (714) 978-2415. 
</P>
<P>
 Researched by JANICE L. JONES / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</TEXT>
