</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Young performers in the jazz, classical and commercial music fields are 
invited to apply for an annual scholarship sponsored by the Orange County 
Musicians' Assn.A total of $3,000 in cash awards will be handed out as part of 
the B. Douglas Sawtelle competition, in addition to the $500 Mick Price 
Scholarship for excellence in jazz. Applicants must be residents of Orange 
County and enrolled as music majors or minors in an accredited a two-year or 
four-year college. The application deadline is April 1. For information, call 
(714) 546-8166. 
</P>
</TEXT>
